HEADWORD: Ludibrious
<hw>Lu*dib"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ludibrium</ets> mockery, derision, from <ets>ludere</ets> to play,
sport.]</ety> <def>Sportive; ridiculous; wanton.</def>
